  "weekly_analysis": "The biggest move this week came from Anthropic's Claude 4 launch, which claimed the top spot in Text Chat, Code Gen, and Reasoning in one shot. An ARC-AGI score of 64.3% marks the first commercial model to systematically surpass the human expert baseline (~60%), signaling a new phase for general reasoning capabilities.\n\nOpenAI announced a 40% price cut on GPT-5 API within 48 hours of Claude 4's release, indicating price competition is intensifying. On the open-source side, DeepSeek V3 holds strong in Code Gen while Llama 4 continues a steady climb in Text Chat.\n\nImage and Video Gen saw no major changes this week — Midjourney v7 and Sora 2 remain on top. Notable: open-source video model Wan 2.1 continues to close the gap with closed-source rivals; its community-contributed LoRA adapters now outnumber Runway's official plugin marketplace.",
